'''Super Bowl Appearances (6)'''<ref>All Super Bowls from I through XLII (1966â2007)</ref> *'''PHI''' (2) â [[Super Bowl XV|1980]], [[Super Bowl XXXIX|2004]] *'''NYG''' (4) â [[Super Bowl XXI|1986]], [[Super Bowl XXV|1990]], [[Super Bowl XXXV|2000]], [[Super Bowl XLII|2007]] |} The '''EaglesâGiants rivalry''' involves the [[National Football League]] teams the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] and the [[New York Giants]]. The rivalry dates back to 1933. However, the competition began to heat up when both teams came to relative prominence in the 1940s and 1950s. The rivalry is mainly based on the two teams being in the same division in the NFL since 1933 and the geographic [[New York City|New York]]-[[Philadelphia]] rivalry. It is ranked by Sports Illustrated as amongst the top ten NFL rivalries of all-time at #4.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/multimedia/photo_gallery/2005/12/15/gallery.oldrivals/content.7.html|title=Top 10 NFL Rivalries Of All Time: No. 4 Giants-Eagles|publisher=si.com}}</ref> However, the geographic rivalry between the Eagles and Giants is well known in football circles, meriting mention on ESPN.com.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/print?id=3086647&type=Columnist&imagesPrint=off|title=Ranking the NFL's best rivalries: Where does Colts-Pats fit?|last=Chadiha|first=Jeffri|publisher=ESPN.com|date=2007-10-31|accessdate=2008-04-12}}</ref>
